"content": "<p>Derived from a Greek word meaning “something which is bottomless” and often used to refer to a place of despair in which demons are imprisoned.</p>\n<h2>The Abyss as a place of despair</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:31\">LUK 8:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:2\">REV 9:2</a></p>\n<h2>The Abyss as the home of demons</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:11\">REV 9:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:8\">REV 17:8</a></p>\n<h2>The Abyss as a prison</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:1\">REV 9:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:1\">REV 20:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:3\">REV 20:3</a></p>",
